Description: A piece from the rim and side of a marl clay pottery vessel. The shape of the surviving piece suggests that it came from a large open vessel like a basin. The rim has an external lip and below it is a ridge.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 19 A
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 19 A scratched into the interior surface.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.97, p.107, p.208, p.219, pl.61)
